  "description": "This dataset comprises processed intracranial EEG recordings from frontal and temporal cortical regions in 13 epilepsy patients performing a load-3 object working memory task. The recordings were obtained from bilateral medial frontal gyrus and middle temporal gyrus, with trials structured to include fixation, encoding, and delay periods. Data have undergone artifact rejection and are provided in concatenated format with accompanying performance metrics and trial indexing information.",
  "methods_description": "Intracranial EEG recordings were collected from frontal (LMFG, RMFG) and temporal (LMTG, RMTG) regions during a load-3 object working memory task. Each trial was 6498 ms in duration, comprising 1000 ms fixation, 1500 ms encoding, and 3998 ms delay periods. Data underwent artifact rejection procedures at the single-trial level. Trials were concatenated into one-dimensional arrays per channel and padded with zeros to ensure uniform data length within subjects.",
